Class BootstrapPaginator

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable<org.apache.wicket.Component>, org.apache.wicket.event.IEventSink, org.apache.wicket.event.IEventSource, org.apache.wicket.IConverterLocator, org.apache.wicket.IGenericComponent<Integer>, org.apache.wicket.markup.html.IHeaderContributor, org.apache.wicket.request.component.IRequestableComponent, org.apache.wicket.util.IHierarchical<org.apache.wicket.Component>, org.apache.wicket.util.io.IClusterable

    public abstract class BootstrapPaginator
extends org.apache.wicket.markup.html.panel.Panel
implements org.apache.wicket.IGenericComponent<Integer>
    This component creates a paginator component using the bootstrap pagination element.

    Example: 

     <nav>
   <ul wicket:id="paginator" class="pagination"></ul>
 </nav>

    The related Java code: 

     new BootstrapPaginator("paginator", Model.of(2000)) {
     public void onPageChange(AjaxRequestTarget target, IModel<Integer> page) {
        ...
     }
 }
    Author:
    acamilo
    See Also:
    bootstrap pagination, Serialized Form
